# Technology Stack Document

## Frontend
- Framework: Next.js (App Router) with TypeScript
- State Management: Zustand / Jotai
- Styling: Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui, Framer Motion (Animations)
- UI Components: Custom, Recharts (Charts)
- Web3 Integration: RainbowKit / Wagmi (for Base Smart Wallet)
- Testing: Jest + React Testing Library (or Vitest + RTL)

## Backend
- Language: Node.js with TypeScript
- Framework: Express.js / Fastify
- AI Integration: Groq API (Chat, Image, potentially Audio) via Backend Proxy
- Real-time: WebSockets (e.g., socket.io)
- Database: Optional MongoDB w/ Mongoose (for user profiles, chat history, etc.)
- API Documentation: Swagger/OpenAPI (Optional)

## DevOps
- CI/CD: GitHub Actions
- Containerization: Docker (Optional)
- Hosting: Vercel (Frontend & Serverless Functions), Fly.io/Railway (Backend), MongoDB Atlas (DB)
- Monitoring: Vercel Analytics / Custom Logging
- Logging: Winston / Pino

## Development Practices
- Version Control: Git (GitHub)
- Code Quality: ESLint + Prettier
- Code Reviews: Required for all PRs
- Testing: Focus on core functionality and API integrations
- Documentation: READMEs, JSDoc/TSDoc comments 